# Zustand: stable selectors only

Returning a fresh object/array from a selector causes the component to
re-render on every store update. Pick a primitive, or wrap with
`useShallow`.

## BAD — fresh array every selector run

```tsx
const messages = useSync((s) => s.messages.filter((m) => m.channelId === id));
```

## GOOD — primitive ref, stable identity

```tsx
const messages = useSync((s) => s.messagesByChannel[id]);
```

## GOOD — derived array via `useShallow`

```tsx
import { useShallow } from "zustand/react/shallow";

const memberIds = useChannel(useShallow((s) => s.members[channelId] ?? []));
```

## Rules

- **Never** call `.map`, `.filter`, `.slice`, or `Object.keys` directly
  inside a `useStore(selector)` callback unless the result is wrapped in
  `useShallow`.
- For multiple values, prefer two `useStore` calls over returning an
  object literal.
- Selectors are pure — derive in `useMemo` outside the store call when
  the input is already stable.
